      "title": "ElizaOS Community Discussion - May 26, 2026",
      "content": [
        {
          "text": "In the general discussion channel, a developer named Thomas Ken posted seeking collaboration opportunities or full-time hiring, sharing their portfolio link. Separately, a user named attic mel returned to the community after a break, asking about the status of the Eliza project. Odilitime, a core developer and moderator, clarified that the labs company is no longer operating but the open source project remains active. Attic mel also noted they had switched back to Linux and could not run JavaScript on their host, suggesting they might revisit the project in about four months. Attic mel additionally flagged a spam issue involving bots inviting users to fake support ticket rooms and requested that moderators develop countermeasures. A separate post from MDMnvest shared a link to an ElizaOS ecosystem fund announcement promoting a predictions game for ElizaOS token holders, described as offering utility for the community.",
